language design: How should array type fields be handled in <, >, <=, >=?

If we improve the ==/!= operators to reason about `type` fields as
proposed in sibling futures to this one, we'll need to decide what to
do about ordered comparison operators.  My instinct would be to have a
type field with runtime type information throw up its hands in the
default compiler-generated comparisons, similar to what we do for
array fields themselves.

#28755
